FORMER Bidvest Wits midfielder Charles Yohane is no more. Yohane was reportedly murdered during a carjacking in Soweto over the weekend. He was 48 at the time of his death and had been working as a driver. Yohane made a name for himself in Mzansi in the colours of Wits where he racked up 268 appearances and scored 44 goals between 1997 and 2006. He finished his playing career in the lower tiers of Mzansi football with FCAK before hanging up his boots in 2008. Yohane represented his country Zimbabwe – earning 23 caps and scoring once. He was part of the Warriors team that participated at the 2004 Africa Cup of Nations (Afcon) in Tunisia – their debut at the competition. He was also part of the team that took part in the 2006 edition before hanging his boots in international football in 2007. He was a coach at the Bidvest Wits development team before the club collapsed in 2020.